"v.辱骂，恶言相向 【英】 v. 辱骂，恶言相向(to use abusive language; rail) 【记】 re(反复)+vile(卑鄙 的，邪恶的)→用邪恶 的话骂→辱骂 【例】 an editorial reviling the Government v. 辱骂 = vituperate 【记】re反, vile(adj 卑鄙的; 邪恶的)一把邪恶的话返回一辱骂 【记】re + vile 卑鄙的, 可耻的, 无价值的；音：歪，不正的，坏的；village 村子，乡下，说谁是乡下来的，乡下人在上海已成了贬低人的话 【相关】vilify 辱骂, 贬低 revile (v.)  c.1300, from Old French reviler ""consider vile, despise, scorn,"" from re-, intensive prefix (see re-), + aviler ""make vile or cheap, disesteem,"" from vil (see vile). Related: Reviled; reviling."
